The paper discusses the use of two open source geospatial big data analytical tools, which involves handling and processing large volumes of data. This makes it likely to fall under the categories of cs.DB (databases), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), and cs.GR (graphics). Additionally, the paper also discusses the architectural comparison of the two tools, which could fall under cs.CE (computer engineering) and cs.SE (software engineering).
